1
00:00:00,221 --> 00:00:07,755
"Let me walk you through a really practical framework I just picked up—the 3-2-1 method—using sunscreen as a case study.

2
00:00:07,755 --> 00:00:17,252
The one core thing you absolutely need to nail about sunscreen isn't the SPF number; it's about applying it generously enough to actually get the protection.

3
00:00:17,252 --> 00:00:22,995
When it comes to formulations, you're essentially looking at two distinct camps.

4
00:00:22,995 --> 00:00:28,162
The first is the classic cream or lotion, which gives you precise coverage.

5
00:00:28,162 --> 00:00:38,184
The second is the spray version, which is a lifesaver for quick reapplication, especially if you're heading for a swim or facing a scorching UV index outdoors.

6
00:00:38,184 --> 00:00:41,434
As for the three actionable steps to find your perfect match:

7
00:00:41,434 --> 00:00:47,618
First, know your skin type—oily, dry, or normal—because that dictates the base.

8
00:00:47,618 --> 00:00:57,675
Second, don't just chase cult favorites like Lancôme, which come with a hefty price tag; take time to explore drugstore alternatives that offer better bang for your buck.

9
00:00:57,675 --> 00:01:00,585
Third, before you rush to place an online order,&nbsp;

10
00:01:00,585 --> 00:01:03,085
consider dropping by a physical store so you can get your hands on it immediately and skip the waiting game.

